  <thing-type id="merten_507601_00_000" listed="false">
    <label>507601 Dual Pole Wall Switch</label>
    <description>Dual Pole Wall Switch&lt;br /&gt&lt;h1&gtOverview&lt;/h1&gt&lt;p&gtThe flush-mounted CONNECT radio receiver with switch will be referred to below as flush-mounted receiver. The flush-mounted receiver can be used to switch loads on and off via radio (for information about permitted loads, see the technical data). When it receives the radio signal, the flush-mounted receiver switches the corresponding contact.CONNECT radio receiver, flush-mounted, 1-gang switch&lt;br /&gt&lt;br /&gtSwitching of ohmic, inductive or capacitive loads. To install in flush-mounted sockets or on a ceiling hook in the ceiling rose.&lt;/p&gt &lt;br /&gt&lt;h2&gtInclusion Information&lt;/h2&gt&lt;p&gtTriple click on the switch button&lt;/p&gt &lt;br /&gt&lt;h2&gtExclusion Information&lt;/h2&gt&lt;p&gtTriple click on the switch button&lt;/p&gt &lt;br /&gt&lt;h2&gtWakeup Information&lt;/h2&gt&lt;p&gtTriple click on the switch button&lt;/p&gt</description>
    <category>WallSwitch</category>

    <!-- CHANNEL DEFINITIONS -->
    <channels>
      <channel id="switch_binary" typeId="switch_binary">
        <label>Switch</label>
        <properties>
          <property name="binding:*:OnOffType">COMMAND_CLASS_SWITCH_BINARY,COMMAND_CLASS_BASIC</property>
        </properties>
      </channel>
    </channels>

